Definitions
* ''Agency" means the Ethiopian Electricity Agency;
<\li2>

Objectives of the Fund
* To provide loan and technical services for Rural Electrification Projects carried out by private operators, cooperatives and local communities and more specifically for those projects operating on renewable energy sources;
	* . To encourage the utilization of electricity for production and social welfare purposes in rural areas.

Sources of Fund
* 1) Budget allocated by the Government;
<\li2>
		* Loans and grants from other Governments;
		* Loans and grants from International Financial InsÂ­titutions;
		* Grants from non-Governmental Organizations;
		* Income from other different sources.

Meetings of the Board
* Extraordinary meetings may be held at any time when called by the chairperson .
* There shall be a quorum where more than half of the members of the Board are present at a meeting.
* Decisons of the Board shall be made valid if more than half of those present voted in favor. In the event of a tie, the chairperson shall have a casting vote.
* The Board may adopt its own rule of procedures with regard to its meetings.
* prepare annual, and whenever required, report and submit it for the approval of the Board;
* review applications from rural electrification project sponsors and based on the criteria approved by the Board decide on the applications;
* set out criteria for the competitive selection of a Trust Agent and submits same to the Board for approval;
* prepare and submit to the Board, for approval, transparent directives and selection criteria and procedures to be used in the issuance of loans and
* facilitate and submit the co-ordination of the rural electrification program activities with other rural development activities;
* promote and support access to and productive use of electricity in the Rural area;
